Grading: This course is graded on the Undergraduate Regular scale.

NEUR 411: Seminar in Neuroscience. 3 credits.
Advanced seminar on a selected topic in neuroscience. Includes in depth reading and discussion of current research in human and nonhuman animals, with an emphasis on critical evaluation. Notes: Course may be repeated if selected topic is different. Offered by Neuroscience. May be repeated within the degree for a maximum 6 credits.
Specialized Designation: Writing Intensive in Major
Registration Restrictions: Required Prerequisites: (ENGH 302C or 302XS) and (NEUR 327C, 327XS, 335C or 335XS).C Requires minimum grade of C.XS Requires minimum grade of XS.
