NEUR 422: Glutamatergic Systems. 3 credits.
A survey of molecular and clinical neuroscience from the perspective of
glutamatergic systems. This course will use the reading of primary scientific literature to guide
students to learn a variety of neural systems, methods in neuroscience, and levels of analysis.
Students will develop critical thinking skills through communicating and critiquing papers. Offered by Neuroscience. Limited to two attempts.
Registration Restrictions: Required Prerequisites: (NEUR 327C or 327XS).C Requires minimum grade of C.XS Requires minimum grade of XS.
Schedule Type: Lecture
Grading: This course is graded on the Undergraduate Regular scale.

NEUR 424: Sleep and Circadian Rhythms. 3 credits.
This course introduces the fields of circadian rhythms with emphasis on sleep including the underlying molecular and genetic machinery, neuroanatomy, and neurophysiology.  The impact of sleep and lack thereof will be explored on diseases and modern society.  Considerable time will be spent reading and analyzing the primary literature in human and animal models. Offered by Neuroscience. Limited to three attempts.
Mason Core: Synthesis
Recommended Prerequisite: NEUR 335
Registration Restrictions: Required Prerequisites: ((BIOL 213C or 213XS) and (PSYC 376C or 376XS)).C Requires minimum grade of C.XS Requires minimum grade of XS.
Schedule Type: Lecture
Grading: This course is graded on the Undergraduate Regular scale.

