NEUR 634: Neural Modeling. 3 credits.
Introduces the objectives, philosophy, and methodology of neuronal modeling. Instructs students in the use of some of the more popular neural modeling software packages. Students learn the syntax of several software packages, how to create neurons from subcellular components, and how to create networks by connecting neuron models. Offered by Neuroscience. May not be repeated for credit.
Recommended Prerequisite: NEUR 602 or permission of instructor.
