NEUR 651: Molecular Neuropharmacology. 3 credits.
Presents key concepts in cellular and molecular neuropharmacology Provides an in-depth survey  of receptor driven cell function, which includes recent topics in cell structure, membrane function, electrical properties of neurons and intracellular signaling. Enables an introduction to research tools and rends in study of neuronal systems via a reading and an analysis of the primary literature.  Offered by Neuroscience. May not be repeated for credit.
