NEUR 701: Neuroscience Laboratory. 3 credits.
Advanced training in experimental techniques used in current neuroscience research. Acquaints students with the theoretical basis of multiple techniques and trains the student in the laboratory skills necessary to perform each technique. Includes work in model systems or cell culture, microscopy, histology and data analysis. Notes: This lab requires working with live zebrafish embryos. Offered by Neuroscience. May not be repeated for credit.
Recommended Prerequisite: NEUR 601 and admission to neuroscience PhD program, or permission of instructor.
